  "title": "Design Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br>\nThe role involves overseeing all design-related activities, ensuring compliance with engineering standards, and providing technical leadership throughout the project lifecycle.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Lead and manage the ACMV design engineering team, ensuring timely and accurate delivery of design packages.</p>\n<p>· Review and approve design drawings, calculations, and technical documents.</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with clients, consultants, and internal teams on design submissions and approvals.</p>\n<p>· Ensure designs meet project specifications, contractual obligations, local codes, and statutory requirements.</p>\n<p>· Provide technical guidance during procurement, installation, testing, and commissioning phases.</p>\n<p>· Identify and resolve design-related issues, proposing cost-effective engineering solutions.</p>\n<p>· Support value engineering and design optimization initiatives.</p>\n<p>· Prepare and present technical reports to project stakeholders.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical Engineering, Building Services Engineering, or equivalent.</p>\n<p>· At least 8–10 years of experience in ACMV design engineering, with 3–5 years in a managerial role.</p>\n<p>· Strong knowledge of HVAC/ACMV system design, load calculations, and equipment selection.</p>\n<p>· Familiarity with relevant codes, standards, and authority submission requirements in Singapore.</p>\n<p>· Proficient in design software such as AutoCAD, Revit, and engineering calculation tools.</p>\n<p>· Excellent leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.</p>\n<p>· Experience in large-scale infrastructure or industrial projects is an advantage.</p>\n<p>· Willingness to work at Tuas area with transportation pickup at designated MRT station.</p>\n<p>· Those with experience in Bentley's Open Building / Microstation software will be an added advantage</p>",
